data.title: University of the East Ramon Magsaysay Memorial Medical Center
data.meta_description:
In 1957, the UE College of Medicine was renamed the “University of the East Ramon Magsaysay Memorial Medical Center” or UERMMMC as a tribute to the late President Ramon Magsaysay who died in a plane crash in Cebu.
	
	(Photo courtesy of National Library)
